Teaching of vocabulary, expressions and speech patterns of modern colloquial Chinese as well as the basic rules of Chinese grammar. Writing, reading and pronouncing of traditional (full shape) Chinese characters. The topics to be learned are: commerce and shopping, studying in the University, hobbies and leisure time, travelling, eating etc. 
In grammar and syntax the rules of succession of the words in a sentence and the dependence of the meaning of a sentence on it, expression of tenses, persons and other grammatical functions in Chinese as well as special functional words and affixes and measure words will be learned. Mastering the writing of characters and calligraphy as well as knowing their etymology will be accented.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Mastering the basics of modern spoken and written Chinese (Mandarin). Practicing reading, conversation (in the limits of topics and vocabulary given in the textbook), and writing characters; learning the basic rules of grammar and syntax of the Chinese language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, the students can:
communicate in Chinese at the elementary level read adapted texts write ca 500 characters of everyday use.
